<div id="Reference-manual-for-Administrative-files"></div>
== Reference manual for Administrative files ==
<div id="index-Administrative-files-_0028reference_0029"></div>
<div id="index-Files_002c-reference-manual"></div>
<div id="index-Reference-manual-_0028files_0029"></div>
<div id="index-CVSROOT-_0028file_0029"></div>

<p>Inside the repository, in the directory
&lsquo;<tt>$CVSROOT/CVSROOT</tt>&rsquo;, there are a number of
supportive files for <small>CVS</small>.  You can use <small>CVS</small> in a limited
fashion without any of them, but if they are set up
properly they can help make life easier.  For a
discussion of how to edit them, see [cvs: The administrative files#Intro-administrative-files The administrative files].
</p>
<p>The most important of these files is the &lsquo;<tt>modules</tt>&rsquo;
file, which defines the modules inside the repository.
</p>
<pre class="menu-preformatted"><nowiki></nowiki>&bull;[cvs: The modules file#modules  modules]::<nowiki>                     Defining modules
</nowiki>&bull;[cvs: The cvswrappers file#Wrappers  Wrappers]::<nowiki>                    Specify binary-ness based on file name
</nowiki>&bull;[cvs: The commit support files#commit-files  commit files]::<nowiki>                The commit support files (commitinfo,
                                verifymsg, editinfo, loginfo)
</nowiki>&bull;[cvs: Rcsinfo#rcsinfo  rcsinfo]::<nowiki>                     Templates for the log messages
</nowiki>&bull;[cvs: Ignoring files via cvsignore#cvsignore  cvsignore]::<nowiki>                   Ignoring files via cvsignore
</nowiki>&bull;[cvs: The checkoutlist file#checkoutlist  checkoutlist]::<nowiki>                Adding your own administrative files
</nowiki>&bull;[cvs: The history file#history-file  history file]::<nowiki>                History information
</nowiki>&bull;[cvs: Expansions in administrative files#Variables  Variables]::<nowiki>                   Various variables are expanded
</nowiki>&bull;[cvs: The CVSROOT%47config configuration file#config  config]::<nowiki>                      Miscellaneous CVS configuration
</nowiki></pre>
